						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Alp wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">what size is optimal for a UxROM game<br /></div>The entire point of using RAM is that there isn't a real threshold for where the memory allocation becomes &quot;unreasonable&quot;.<br /><br />As a vague rule of thumb, I'd probably say &quot;not more than half of the entire game data for CHR&quot;, but if you're planning on making hardware, all of 128, 256, and 512 KiB PROMs are approximately the same cost nowadays ($1 to $1.50), and there's no real disadvantage to filling as much as you have use for.</div>

